A report about incarceration in the Washington state using the incarceration_trends.csv in this GitHub repository.

Introduction:

Incarceration is a major topic in the United States (U.S.). Using the incarceration_trends.csv in this GitHub repository can help us visualize the current incarceration issue in the U.S. as it contains substantial information about the incarceration in the U.S. from 1970 to 2018. To analyse this data with more detail, I would examine how does race act as a factor in the incarceration. In our data ethic lecture we have crossed similar topics in which the machine learning tool in the past had mistakenly rated African Americans with higher risk compared to other race Americans without evidence. Eventually, in this report, I will examine the race factor with respect to incarceration in the U.S. state and conclude my observations below.

There are some questions in which I hope to answer in my summary information section:

  • How many rows and columns are in this data-set?

  • Which area has the highest jail population?

  • Which urbanisity has the highest jail population?

  • How many people are in jail over the years?

  • How many African Americans are in jail over the years in the U.S.?

  • How many white people are in jail over the years in the U.S.?

  • How many Latino Americans are in jail over the years in the U.S.?

  • How many Asian Americans are in jail over the years in the U.S.?

Summary Information:

To further calculate how does race act as a factor to affect the incarceration in the U.S., I have used analytical and DPLYR skills to calculate important summary values that I think is relevant to my exploration. There are 153811 rows and 121 columns in the dataset. The area with highest jail population is South. The urbanicity with highest jail population is small/mid. The total population that goes to jail over the years is 23207908, the total black population in jail over the years is 7891239. To compared with other races, the total white population in jail is 8814789, the total latinx population in jail over the years is 3220014, and the total asian population in jail over the years is 192596. Observing those data, we can see that the highest population that goes to jail by race would be white.

Trends over time chart:

For trends over the time chart, I want to know how does the population of different races increase in jail as time goes on. By using a scatter plot, we can easily visualize how does population of different races increase in jail. The graph is generated below.

Note we can see that the black and white population in jail are similar, whereas the latino and asian population are the latter two.

Variable comparison chart

I did a scatter line plot between 2 variables, and the purpose of this chart is to show the black population in jail and the black population to compare about the black population in jail and not in jail. One important observation I can derive from this chart is that even though the population is increasing drastically, but the population in jail only increase a little bit relatively. Therefore, one can reasonablly conclude that only a little out of the black population are in jail.

Map

The purpose of this chart is to show the black population density in jail in 2017 as the year has enough data to perform this chart. The lighter the blue the more black population in jail. So we can see that the Mideast region has the highest black population in jail. Whereas some of the states in the shape of hexagon do not have black jail population, thus it is making the color of gray. Note: I have used code from here for making the chart below.
